üìò Summary: The Phases of the Data Analysis Process

The data analysis process has six phases:
Ask ‚Üí Prepare ‚Üí Process ‚Üí Analyze ‚Üí Share ‚Üí Act
Each step builds on the last to turn raw data into meaningful decisions.

1Ô∏è‚É£ Ask Phase

The foundation of the entire analysis.
Analysts must:
Understand stakeholder expectations
Define the problem
Create clear, focused questions

This phase ensures the analyst knows what is needed, why, and how the results will be used.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Prepare Phase

The goal is to find the right data. Analysts:
Identify sources
Decide what data is useful
Ensure data is unbiased and objective
Good analysis starts with the right data, not just any data.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Process Phase

This phase cleans and improves the data so it‚Äôs ready to analyze. Analysts:
Clean errors
Reformat or transform data
Combine datasets
Remove outliers
They also verify that cleaned data is correct, complete, and trustworthy.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Analyze Phase

Now the cleaned data becomes insightful information. Analysts:
Look for trends, relationships, and patterns
Use tools like spreadsheets, SQL, and R
Answer the questions defined in the Ask phase
This is where the real decision-making value begins.

5Ô∏è‚É£ Share Phase

Analysts communicate insights to stakeholders using:
Data stories
Visualizations
Dashboards
Reports
Clear communication helps stakeholders understand the results and make data-driven decisions.

6Ô∏è‚É£ Act Phase

The final step: put insights into action.
In this program, the "act" phase is:
Completing a case study
Adding it to your portfolio
Preparing for the job search
This is where everything you learn becomes practical and valuable.

üéì How Each Course in the Program Fits Into the Process
Phase	Course
Ask	Ask Questions to Make Data-Driven Decisions
Prepare	Prepare Data for Exploration
Process	Process Data from Dirty to Clean
Analyze	Analyze Data to Answer Questions / R Programming
Share	Share Data Through Visualization / R Programming
Act	Capstone Case Study
‚≠ê Key Takeaway

The six-phase data analysis process gives you a roadmap for turning raw data into insights that drive decisions.
Each phase is essential, and the Google Data Analytics program is designed to teach you each part step by step.
